R & Statistics:
----------------
Statistics for Biology in R: Modern Statistics for Modern Biology from Susan Holmes and Wolfgang Huber
  - also has for example a whole chapter on ggplot
  - available at https://web.stanford.edu/class/bios221/book/introduction.html

Using bash and command line tools
--------------------------------
The Biostar Handbook: Your Bioinformatics Data Analysis Guide from Istvan Albert
  - step-by-step introduction into command line processing of biological data
  - You can ask Kathi for the ebook

Maschine learning intro
------------------------
An Introduction to Statistical Learning with Applications in R
 - the theory behind most basic techniques
- pdf is freely available, ask Melina


